<|channel>thought
<channel|>After a heavy summer downpour, the sky over the hills is a soft, misty grey. The air smells of wet grass and damp earth. I love waiting by the window, watching the raindrops race down the glass.

Then, the sun peeks through the clouds. It is a bright, golden light that makes everything sparkle. Suddenly, there it is—a magnificent rainbow stretching across the valley.

My favourite rainbows are the ones that look like they are painted with thick, bright strokes. They aren't faint or shy; they are bold and proud. The red is as deep as a strawberry, the yellow is as warm as a lemon, and the violet is as rich as a plum. 

The colours arch perfectly from one green hill to the next, as if a giant has dropped a colourful ribbon across the sky. It makes the whole world feel magical and new. I stand there, breathless, watching the colours glow against the retreating storm clouds, waiting for the next adventure to begin. [end of text]


